"Danard M.B., Dube S.K., Gönnert G., Munroe A., Murty T.S., Chittibabu P., Rao A.D., Sinha P.C.","Storm surges from extra-tropical cyclones",2004,"Natural Hazards","32","2",,"177","190",,,10.1023/B:NHAZ.0000031312.98231.81,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-2942657129&partnerID=40&md5=258f9d65b81881136c4bbc644e2ce632","Atmospheric Dynamics Corporation, 271 Trevlac Place, Victoria, BC V9E 2C4, Canada; Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, India; Department of Port/River Engineering, Dalmannstr. 1-3, 20457 Hamburg, Germany; Environment Waikato, P.O. Box 4010, Hamilton East, New Zealand; W.F. Baird/Associates Coastal Eng., 1145 Hunt Club Road, Ottawa, Ont. K1V 0Y3, Canada; Centre for Atmospheric Sciences, Indian Institute of Technology, Hauz Khas, New Delhi 110 016, India","Danard, M.B., Atmospheric Dynamics Corporation, 271 Trevlac Place, Victoria, BC V9E 2C4, Canada; Dube, S.K., Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, India; Gönnert, G., Department of Port/River Engineering, Dalmannstr. 1-3, 20457 Hamburg, Germany; Munroe, A., Environment Waikato, P.O. Box 4010, Hamilton East, New Zealand; Murty, T.S., W.F. Baird/Associates Coastal Eng., 1145 Hunt Club Road, Ottawa, Ont. K1V 0Y3, Canada; Chittibabu, P., W.F. Baird/Associates Coastal Eng., 1145 Hunt Club Road, Ottawa, Ont. K1V 0Y3, Canada; Rao, A.D., Centre for Atmospheric Sciences, Indian Institute of Technology, Hauz Khas, New Delhi 110 016, India; Sinha, P.C., Centre for Atmospheric Sciences, Indian Institute of Technology, Hauz Khas, New Delhi 110 016, India","The possible influence of climate change on the tracks of the extra-tropical cyclones as well as storm surges is studied. Two different data bases have been used: one for the Great Lakes of North America and the other for the German Bight in the North Sea of Europe. For the Great Lakes region, significant east-west and north-south shifts in the tracks of ETC'S with decadal periodicities have been observed. However, there was no trend in the amplitudes of storm surges. The most important result for the Great Lakes is that, depending upon its position relative to the constantly shifting storm tracks, a given location could either experience a major storm surge or could miss out completely. The storm surges in the German Bight in general, and at Cuxhaven in particular, appear to show a slightly increasing trend in the latter part of the 20th century. However, the most significant result for the German Bight is that the number of storm tides (i.e., multiple peaks in a given storm surge event) definitely has shown an increase in the second half of the 20th century. This increase is interpreted as due to the influence of meso-scale weather systems embedded in the synoptic scale ETCs. © 2004 Kluwer Academic Publishers.","Embankment; Extra-tropical cyclone; Flood; Global warming; Hazard mitigation; Storm surge; Total water level","climate change; cyclone; extratropical environment; flooding; global warming; storm surge; storm track; twentieth century; Atlantic Ocean; German Bight; Great Lakes; North America; North Sea",,,,,,"Danard, M.B., On the influence of released latent heat on cyclone development (1964) J. Appl. Meteorol., 3, pp. 27-37; Dietrich, G., Kalle, K., Krauss, W., Siedler, G., (1975) Allgemeine Meereskande, , Berlin; Gönnert, G., Dube, S.K., Murty, T., Siefert, W., (2001) Global Storm Surge, Theory, Observations and Applications, Die Küste, 63, p. 623; Gönnert, G., Ferk, U., Natürliche und anthropogen beeinflußte Entwicklung von Sturmfluten in der Deutschen Bucht und der Unterelbe (1997) Vechtaer Studien Zur Angewandten Geographie und Regionalwissenschaft, 18 S, pp. 13-31; Gönnert, G., Veränderung des Charakters von Sturmfluten in der Nordsee aufgrund von Klimaänderung in den letzten 100 Jahren (1999) Marburger Geographische Schriften, 134, pp. 24-39; Gönnert, G., Siefert, W., Storm surge development in the Southern North Sea and the Elbe river in Europe during the last century and its practical application (1997) Mausam, 48, pp. 499-514; Graham, N.E., Diaz, H.F., Evidence for intensification of North Pacific winter cyclones since 1948 (2001) Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc., 82, pp. 1869-1893; Grassl, H., Globaler, W., (1993) Klimaänderung und Küste. Einblick Ins Treibhaus, pp. 28-37. , H. J. Schellhuber und H. Sterr (Hg.), S, Berlin; Grassl, H., Klingholz, R., (1990) Wir Klimamacher - Auswege Aus Dem Globalen Treibhaus, pp. 296S. , Frankfurt, Main; Climate change. Impacts, adaptation, and vulnerability (2001), pp. 2-64. , IPCC: J. T. Houghton, G. J. Jenkins, and J. J. Ephruams (eds.), Cambridge University Press, CambridgeLander-Arbeitsgruppe, A., Bemessungswasserstände entlang der Elbe (1988) Die Küste, 47, pp. 31-50; Lewis, P.J., Severe storms over the Great Lakes: A catalogue summary for the period 1957 to 1985 (1987), Canadian Climate Center, Report number 87-13, Atmospheric Environment Service. Downsview, Ontario, CanadaList Robert, J., (1968) Smithsonian Meteorological Tables, 527. , Smithsonian Institution Press, City of Washington; Murty, T.S., (1984) Storm Surges, Meteorological Ocean Tides, , Ottawa; Sellinger, C.E., Quinn, F.H., (1999) Proceedings of the Great Lakes Paleo-Levels Workshop The Last 4000 Years, p. 43. , Great Lakes Environmental Research Laboratory, NOAA. Ann Arbor, MI; Siefert, W., Sturmflutvorhersage für den Tidebereich der Elbe aus dem Verlauf der Windstaukurve in Cuxhaven (1968) Mitteilungen des Franzius-Instituts für Grund- und Wasserbau Der Technischen Universität Hannover, 30, pp. 1-42; Siefert, W., (1985) Sturmfluten Von 1901 Bis 1984 Vor Der Südlichen Nordseeküste Und in Hamburg (Ganglinien), 44. , Hamburger Küstenforschung, Hamburg; Siefert, W., Bemessungswasserstände 2085A entlang der Elbe. Ergebnisse einer Überprüfung durch die Lünderarbeitsgruppe nach 10 Jahren 1995, 1996 (1998) Die Küste, 60, pp. 227-255; Werner, P.C., Gerstengarbe, F.W., Fraedrich, K., Oesterle, H., Recent climate change in the North Atlantic (2001